{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_35","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"WARNING\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P2\",\"location\":\"src/app/api/livekit/token/route.ts:172\",\"description\":\"BANNED guard exempts any user who is also Space.ownerId (`!space && ...`). That leaves a reachable bypass for a BANNED owner: socket join blocks `member.restriction === \\\"BANNED\\\"` unconditionally, and the admin members route only protects OWNER from non-superAdmin actions, so a superAdmin can still create an OWNER+BANNED state. Such a user can then obtain a LiveKit token directly and rejoin media.\",\"recommendation\":\"Make the token route reject `spaceMember?.restriction === \\\"BANNED\\\"` regardless of owner status, or enforce owner-ban impossibility at the mutation boundary and add a regression test for owner+BANNED token denial/immutability.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true}]}"}}
